f set."},"2283":{"id":"/integration-webhook-64","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#retry-reconciliation--failure-handling","content":"Webhook-driven flows in DeepDoc are designed for idempotency and resilience:"},"2284":{"id":"/integration-webhook-65","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#retry-reconciliation--failure-handling","content":"Corpus Rebuild on Failure:In ChatbotIndexer.sync_incremental() (deepdoc/chatbot/indexer.py:60), if a previous full sync failed or a corpus is missing/inconsistent, the handler triggers a full rebuild for that corpus:"},"2285":{"id":"/integration-webhook-66","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#retry-reconciliation--failure-handling","content":"Embedding Retry Logic:The embedding client (LiteLLMEmbeddingClient.embed(), deepdoc/chatbot/providers.py:60) handles context window errors by splitting batches or trimming text, and retries as needed."},"2286":{"id":"/integration-webhook-67","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#retry-reconciliation--failure-handling","content":"Error Propagation:If embedding or chat completion fails, exceptions are raised with actionable hints (e.g., missing API key, model error). These are surfaced to the CLI or API caller."},"2287":{"id":"/integration-webhook-68","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#retry-reconciliation--failure-handling","content":"No Explicit Circuit Breaker:There is no explicit circuit breaker or exponential backoff in the provided code, but the design ensures that failed or partial updates do not corrupt the corpus and can be retried safely."},"2288":{"id":"/integration-webhook-69","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"Batch Size Limits:Embedding batch size is provider-dependent (batch_size in config, default 1 for Azure, 24 otherwise). Large payloads may be split automatically."},"2289":{"id":"/integration-webhook-70","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"CORS and Origins:If running the backend locally, ensure DEEPDOC_CHATBOT_PREVIEW_PORT is set so that the frontend can communicate with the backend during preview."},"2290":{"id":"/integration-webhook-71","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"Partial Syncs:If a webhook triggers an update for a file that is not tracked or already deleted, the handler will skip it gracefully."},"2291":{"id":"/integration-webhook-72","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"Embedding Model Identity:The embedding metadata includes the model identity (provider, model, base_url, api_version) for traceability."},"2292":{"id":"/integration-webhook-73","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"No Built-in Rate Limiting:The code does not implement explicit rate limiting for webhook-triggered updates; ensure your external systems do not overwhelm the backend with events."},"2293":{"id":"/integration-webhook-74","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"type: warn"},"2294":{"id":"/integration-webhook-75","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/integration-webhook#operational-gotchas","content":"If the embedding provider returns a \"context window\" or \"maximum context length\" error, the system will attempt to split or trim the input and retry. However, repeated failures may require manual intervention."},"2295":{"id":"/integration-webhook-76","page_id":"/integration-webhook","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/in