ntent":"Quick Reference"},"2326":{"id":"/parsing-analysis-25","page_id":"/parsing-analysis","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/parsing-analysis#constants-enums--status-values","content":"Constants, Enums & Status Values"},"2327":{"id":"/parsing-analysis-26","page_id":"/parsing-analysis","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/parsing-analysis#see-also","content":"See Also"},"2328":{"id":"/parsing-analysis-27","page_id":"/parsing-analysis","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/parsing-analysis#overview","content":"The Parsing & Source Analysis feature is responsible for extracting structured information from source code files across supported languages and frameworks. Its core purpose is to transform raw source files (such as Vue SFCs, JavaScript, or TypeScript modules) into a normalized, analyzable representation (ParsedFile) containing symbols, imports, and documentation artifacts. This enables downstream documentation generation, code navigation, and integration with planning and site-building workflows."},"2329":{"id":"/parsing-analysis-28","page_id":"/parsing-analysis","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/parsing-analysis#overview","content":"Parsing is a foundational step in the Pipeline: Document Generation & Planning, providing the raw evidence and symbol tables that power DeepDoc's automated documentation. It is also tightly integrated with Vue Component Parsing and Integration for frontend codebases."},"2330":{"id":"/parsing-analysis-29","page_id":"/parsing-analysis","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/parsing-analysis#overview","content":"Parsing is the first stage in DeepDoc's evidence pipeline. All downstream documentation, planning, and site generation depend on the accuracy and completeness of this step."},"2331":{"id":"/parsing-analysis-30","page_id":"/parsing-analysis","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/parsing-analysis#overview","content":"For a high-level view of how parsing fits into the overall system, see DeepDoc Architecture & Overview."},"2332":{"id":"/parsing-analy