s the backend for the chatbot UI, handling natural language queries, retrieving relevant code/doc chunks, and generating answers using LLMs."],[595,"The DeepDoc CLI (deepdoc/cli.py) is the primary interface for generating, updating, previewing, and deploying documentation for your codebase. It orchestrates the full documentation lifecycle, from initializing project config to serving a live preview and deploying a static site. The CLI is tightly integrated with DeepDoc's planning, generation, and site-building pipeline, and interacts with LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Azure), chatbot APIs (Deepdoc Chat API), and embedding services (Deepdoc Embed API)."],[2035,"The Deepdoc Embed API is a required dependency for all chatbot and retrieval features. If not configured, code search and context-aware answers will not function."],[2036,"The Deepdoc Embed API is referenced and used in several key locations:"],[2058,"The Deepdoc Embed API is used by the following features and endpoints:"],[2030,"The Deepdoc Embed API provides vector embedding services for DeepDoc's code and artifact retrieval features. It is responsible for transforming code snippets, documentation, and other textual artifacts into vector representations, enabling semantic search, similarity matching, and context retrieval for the DeepDoc Chatbot and documentation generation pipeline."],[1878,"The default model is claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022. Model upgrades may change output style or capabilities."],[1727,"The detected frameworks shape how DeepDoc parses, analyzes, and documents your codebase. See Setup & Getting Started for environment and dependency details."],[1068,"The development notes in README.md directly inform the following areas:"],[2507,"The Document Generation & Planning pipeline is the heart of DeepDoc's documentation system. It orchestrates the transformation of raw repository artifacts (source files, config, endpoints, integrations, and markdown context) into a structured, validated, and cros